  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Treatment of venous thromboembolism in cancer patients is specific and has been validated in
      trials that favor the use of LMWH (Low Molecular Weight Heparin) instead of VKA (Vitamin K
      Antagonist) treatment during 6 months. International recommendations have diffused this
      option.It is necessary to evaluate the compliance of physicians to this treatment by
      measuring the number of patients with cancer treated with long term use of LMWH.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
